 
<p>

  <a href="https://robertreich.substack.com/p/what-happens-when-supermajorities">Supermajorities enable parties to crush democracy</a>, as
Republican parties are doing now in several states.
<p>
But these supermajorities did not happen naturally.  They result from
Republican measures to rig elections &mdash; <a href="https://stallman.org/archives/2022-jul-oct.html#31_October_2022_(Republicans_propose_federal_laws_to_make_voting_more_difficult)">voter suppression</a>
and <a href="https://stallman.org/archives//2021-sep-dec.html#20_November_2021_(Gerrymandering)">gerrymandering</a>.

 